  <title>Heap and Memory Management</title>

  <introduction>
    <p> In this chapter, we will explore how memory is managed in C++ programs, focusing on the heap
      and stack, dynamic memory allocation, and the associated challenges such as memory leaks and
      segmentation faults. </p>
    <p>We will also learn about a strategy for dealing with the complexities of memory management:
      container classes.</p>
  </introduction>

